# Journal ↔ Salary Negotiation Link

## Context
- `journal/YYYY/MM/DD.md` contains daily work logs with a **Business Impact** section
- `10-soft-skills/interviewing/salary-negotiation-leverage.md` contains the salary negotiation preparation doc with an **Evidence Log** table

## When writing or updating a journal entry

1. **Always include a "Business Impact" section** after "What I Worked On"
2. Reframe technical work in business/CEO language using these categories:
   - 🚀 Shipped: [feature] → [who benefits and how]
   - ⚡ Unblocked: [what was stuck] → [now the team/business can...]
   - 🛡️ Prevented: [risk/bug] → [what would have happened without this fix]
   - 📈 Accelerated: [process] → [estimated time/cost saved]
3. **After writing Business Impact**, automatically append a one-liner summary for each SNDQ item to the **Evidence Log** table in `10-soft-skills/interviewing/salary-negotiation-leverage.md`
4. Evidence Log format: `| Date | What happened | Business impact |`

## Framing rules (Ben = CEO, values delivery speed)
- Frame everything as business value, NOT technical achievement
- "Shipped feature X across Y modules" > "Refactored component Z"
- "Fixed blocker that stopped all deployments" > "Resolved heap memory issue"
- "Reducing build time so team ships faster" > "Found circular dependency"
- Always answer: "So what? How does this help the business?"

## Also track in Business Impact
- Turnaround time (assigned → shipped)
- Independence level (did you need handholding?)
- Cross-module scope (how many areas touched?)
- Multiplier effect (how many people/processes unblocked?)
